SAMPLES.DESCRIPTION: An example report returned in JSON format

PARAMETERS.NAME: reportReference
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: The reference for the desired report. This can be found by either querying the api/report/list API, or as the ref parameter in the URL when running the report in aXcelerate. For example, for the Contact Details report is the value is: contactsSimple

PARAMETERS.DEFAULT: Each report has default view fields
PARAMETERS.NAME: selectedViewFields
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: A comma-separated list of field names to include in the report. The list of available fields can be found for a report by querying the api/report/fields API. An example value could be: vmcontacts.surname, vmcontacts.givenName

PARAMETERS.NAME: selectedFilterFields
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: A JSON representation of an array of filter structs to pass to the report. The structs must have the keys: name, value, and operator. For a list of available filters for a report, query the API api/report/fields. For a more comprehensive list of the values and operators available for a field, query the API api/report/field and pass the field name as 'fieldReference'. The string is not case sensitive. An example value for the contactsSimple report, to return all contacts with the surname 'Jones' would be: [{name:'vmcontacts.surname', value:'Jones', operator:'IS'}]

PARAMETERS.NAME: reportID
PARAMETERS.DESCRIPTION: If passed, this endpoint acts the same as api/report/saved/run.

DESCRIPTION:
Interacts with the aXcelerate Report Builder. You can run any* Report , provide selected view fields and filters and it will return the results in JSON format.

List of reports that is not intended for API :
1/Recognised Revenue report
2/Recognised Revenue Summary report
